  "doc_id": "19528",
  "text": "14 Isolate identification alone does not change care, but it can influence the therapeutic decisionmaking process by accounting for potential drug resistance. [CITATION_1] Even though the NAP1 strain may have reduced role in the USA nowadays, this strain is still found to predict clinical outcomes in patients with CDI. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Further studies are needed to determine whether the NAP1 strain or other strains are the reasons for more severe disease in children.",
